natural_language_question:
For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all enzymes in UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot annotated to catalyze reactions involving that lipid.
This query does not consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions and enzymes only for the specified lipid.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

# Example 16
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?uniprot
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?startId owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
  # federated query to UniProt
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?uniprot up:reviewed true .
    ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
  }
} 
ORDER BY ?startId
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX uniprot: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/annotation/>
PREFIX swisslipid: <http://www.swisslipids.org/rdf/>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uniprotEntry ?uniprotName
WHERE {
  # Step 1: Find the ChEBI identifier corresponding to the given SWISSLIPID in the SwissLipids endpoint.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/> {
    swisslipid:000399814 swisslipid:has_chebi ?chebiID .
  }

  # Step 2: In the Rhea endpoint (the primary endpoint for this query), find reactions
  # that involve the chemical entity identified by the ChEBI ID found in Step 1.
  # A reaction involves a chemical if it is present on either the left or right side.
  ?reaction rhea:side ?side .
  ?side rhea:contains ?chebiID .

  # Step 3: Find the UniProt entry that catalyzes the reaction found in Step 2.
  ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?uniprotEntry .

  # Step 4: In the UniProt endpoint, check if the UniProt entry found in Step 3
  # is a reviewed entry (i.e., from UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot).
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?uniprotEntry a uniprot:Protein . # Ensure the entry is a protein
    ?uniprotEntry up:reviewed true . # Filter for Swiss-Prot entries
    # Optional: Retrieve the recommended full name for the UniProt entry
    OPTIONAL { ?uniprotEntry uniprot:recommendedName/uniprot:fullName ?uniprotName }
  }
}

natural_language_question:
For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all corresponding reactions (Rhea IDs and equation).
This query does consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions involving the specified lipid and/or its more specific forms.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>

# Example 5
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?id ?name ?chebi ?rhea ?rheaEquation 
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # Retrieve children lipids 
  ?id rdfs:subClassOf* ?startId .
  ?id rdfs:label ?name .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?id owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:equation ?rheaEquation .
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
} 
ORDER BY  ?startId ?id
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/
PREFIX sl: <http://purl.swisslipids.org/sl/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?rheaID ?equation
WHERE {
  # Query the SwissLipids endpoint to find the specified lipid and its subclasses
  SERVICE <https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/> {
    # Define the starting lipid resource URI
    BIND(sl:SWISSLIPID:000399814 AS ?startLipid)

    # Find the starting lipid itself OR any lipid that is a subclass (directly or indirectly)
    # of the starting lipid. This covers the "more specific forms" requirement.
    { ?specificLipid rdfs:subClassOf* ?startLipid }
    UNION
    { BIND(?startLipid AS ?specificLipid) } # Include the starting lipid resource itself

    # Find Rhea reactions that involve these specific lipids.
    # Assuming sl:involvedIn is the property linking lipids to Rhea reactions in SwissLipids.
    ?specificLipid sl:involvedIn ?rheaReaction .
  }

  # Federate to the Rhea endpoint to get details about the found reactions
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/> {
    # Ensure the resource is a Rhea Reaction (optional but good practice)
    ?rheaReaction a rhea:Reaction .

    # Extract the Rhea ID from the reaction URI
    BIND(STRAFTER(STR(?rheaReaction), STR(rhea:)) AS ?rheaID)

    # Get the reaction equation
    ?rheaReaction rhea:equation ?equation .
  }
}

natural_language_question: What are the Homo sapiens genes associated with cancer and their orthologs expressed in the Rattus norvegicus brain?
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX disease: <http://purl.uniprot.org/diseases/>
PREFIX BTO: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BTO_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT ?hs_gene ?hs_gene_name ?rn_gene ?rn_gene_name
WHERE {
  # This query is executed against the UniProt endpoint, and all required data
  # is available within this endpoint. The SERVICE clause is used as required
  # by the task, even though it queries the same endpoint.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Find proteins in Homo sapiens (taxon:9606)
    ?hs_protein up:organism taxon:9606 .

    # Filter for proteins associated with Cancer (disease:162 in Disease Ontology)
    ?hs_protein up:classifiedWith disease:162 .

    # Get the corresponding Homo sapiens gene and its name
    ?hs_protein up:encodedBy ?hs_gene .
    ?hs_gene rdfs:label ?hs_gene_name .

    # Find orthologs of these Homo sapiens proteins
    ?hs_protein up:ortholog ?rn_protein .

    # Ensure the ortholog is in Rattus norvegicus (taxon:10116)
    ?rn_protein up:organism taxon:10116 .

    # Check if the Rattus norvegicus ortholog is expressed in the brain (BTO:0000139)
    ?rn_protein up:expressedIn BTO:0000139 .

    # Get the corresponding Rattus norvegicus gene and its name
    ?rn_protein up:encodedBy ?rn_gene .
    ?rn_gene rdfs:label ?rn_gene_name .
  }
}

natural_language_question: Find all proteins linked to arachidonate (CHEBI:32395)
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>


SELECT 
    DISTINCT
        ?uniprot
        ?uniprotID
        ?recname
        ?gene
        ?chebi
        ?uniprotName
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
     VALUES (?chebi) { (CHEBI:32395) }
     ?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
     ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
     ?chebi up:name ?uniprotName .
  }
  ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
  ?uniprot up:mnemonic ?uniprotID .
  ?uniprot up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?recname .
  OPTIONAL {?uniprot up:encodedBy/skos:prefLabel ?gene .}
}
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX uniprot: <http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?protein ?proteinName
WHERE {
  # Query Rhea to find reactions involving arachidonate (CHEBI:32395)
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Find reactions that have a participant role linked to CHEBI:32395
    ?reaction rhea:hasParticipant ?participantRole .
    ?participantRole rhea:chemical chebi:32395 .

    # Find the entity that catalyzes this reaction.
    # Rhea links catalyzedBy to UniProt entries or EC numbers.
    # We are interested in UniProt entries for protein details.
    ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?protein .

    # Ensure the catalyzedBy entity is a UniProt protein URI
    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?protein), "http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/"))
  }

  # Query UniProt to get the name of the protein found in Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?protein a uniprot:Protein ;
             skos:prefLabel ?proteinName . # Get the recommended protein name
  }
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve human enzymes that metabolize sphingolipids and are annotated in ChEMBL

Retrieve the UniProtKB proteins, their catalyzed Rhea reactions, their encoding genes (Ensembl) and the anatomic entities where the genes are expressed (UBERON anatomic entites from Bgee expression data resource).
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX bgee: <http://purl.org/bgee/public#>
PREFIX faldo: <http://biohackathon.org/resource/faldo#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?protein ?rheaReaction ?ensemblGene ?uberonEntity
WHERE {
  # Query UniProt for proteins, their catalyzed reactions, and encoding genes (Ensembl)
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Find UniProt proteins
    ?protein a up:Protein .

    # Find Rhea reactions catalyzed by the protein
    ?protein up:catalyzedReaction ?rheaReaction .

    # Link the protein to its gene resource and find the Ensembl cross-reference
    # UniProt links proteins to gene resources via up:gene
    ?protein up:gene ?gene .
    # The gene resource has cross-references to external databases like Ensembl via rdfs:seeAlso
    ?gene rdfs:seeAlso ?ensemblGene .
    # Ensure the cross-reference URI is from Ensembl
    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?ensemblGene), "http://rdf.ebi.ac.uk/resource/ensembl/"))
  }

  # Query Bgee for expression data linked to the Ensembl gene and anatomic entity (UBERON)
  # Bgee provides gene expression data linked to genes and anatomic locations (UBERON)
  SERVICE <https://sparql.bgee.org/sparql> {
    # Find expression data entries
    ?expression bgee:Expression ?expressionType . # Match any type of expression data (e.g., presence/absence)
    # Link the expression data to the Ensembl gene found in UniProt
    ?expression bgee:expressionFoundInGene ?ensemblGene .
    # Get the anatomic entity (UBERON) where the expression is found
    ?expression bgee:expressionFoundInAnatEntity ?uberonEntity .
    # Ensure the anatomic entity URI is from UBERON
    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?uberonEntity), "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_"))
  }
}

natural_language_question: Find mouse homologs in OMABrowser of human enzymes that catalyze reactions involving sterols (CHEBI:15889). Federating with Rhea and OMABrowser.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

SELECT
  DISTINCT
    ?chebi
    ?reaction
    ?humanProtein
    ?mouseProtein
    ?cluster 
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
    ?reaction rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
    ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
    ?chebi rdfs:subClassOf* CHEBI:15889
  }

  ?humanProtein up:organism taxon:9606 .
  ?humanProtein up:annotation ?a .
  ?a a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation .
  ?a up:catalyticActivity ?ca .
  ?ca up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction .

  SERVICE  <https://sparql.omabrowser.org/sparql> {
    ?cluster a orth:ParalogsCluster .
    ?cluster orth:hasHomologousMember ?node1 , ?node2 .
    ?node1 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?orthoProtein1 .
    ?node2 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?orthoProtein2 .
    ?orthoProtein1 lscr:xrefUniprot ?mouseProtein .
    ?orthoProtein2 lscr:xrefUniprot ?humanProtein .
    # inTaxon mouse
    ?orthoProtein1 orth:organism/<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162> taxon:10090 . 
  }
}
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX oma: <http://sparql.omabrowser.org/ontology#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?mouseHomolog ?humanEnzyme
WHERE {
  # Step 1: Find reactions in Rhea involving sterols (CHEBI:15889)
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction rhea:hasParticipant ?participant .
    ?participant rhea:chebi chebi:15889 . # CHEBI:15889 corresponds to 'sterol'
    ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?humanEnzyme . # Get the enzyme (UniProt ID) catalyzing the reaction
  }

  # Step 2: Verify that the enzyme found in Rhea is from human using UniProt
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?humanEnzyme a up:Protein .
    ?humanEnzyme up:organism taxon:9606 . # Filter for human proteins (Taxonomy ID 9606)
  }

  # Step 3: Find mouse homologs of these human enzymes using OMABrowser
  SERVICE <https://sparql.omabrowser.org/sparql> {
    # Find the OMA group that the human enzyme belongs to
    ?humanEnzyme oma:memberOf ?omaGroup . # Link the human protein (identified by UniProt ID) to its OMA group

    # Find other members of the same OMA group that are from mouse
    ?mouseHomolog oma:memberOf ?omaGroup .
    ?mouseHomolog up:organism taxon:10090 . # Filter for mouse proteins (Taxonomy ID 10090)

    # Ensure the found homolog is distinct from the original human enzyme (different species)
    FILTER (?mouseHomolog != ?humanEnzyme)
  }
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve drugs that target human enzymes involved in sterol metabolism (federated query with Rhea and ChEMBL via IDSM/Elixir czech republic).
predicted_query:
# https://idsm.elixir.cz/sparql
PREFIX chembl: <http://rdf.ebi.ac.uk/schema/chembl#>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?drug ?drugName
WHERE {
  # --- Query ChEMBL endpoint to find drugs and their protein targets ---
  SERVICE <https://idsm.elixir.cz/sparql> {
    # Find entities that are classified as Drugs
    ?drug a chembl:Drug .
    # Get the preferred label (name) of the drug
    ?drug skos:prefLabel ?drugName .
    # Find the activity associated with the drug
    ?drug chembl:hasActivity ?activity .
    # Find the target of the activity
    ?activity chembl:hasTarget ?target .
    # Find the target component, which is often a protein
    ?target chembl:hasTargetComponent ?targetComponent .
    # Link the target component to its corresponding UniProt protein URI
    ?targetComponent chembl:hasProtein ?proteinURI .
  }

  # --- Query UniProt endpoint to check if the protein target is human and an enzyme ---
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Ensure the URI is indeed a UniProt Protein entry
    ?proteinURI a up:Protein .
    # Check if the protein is from Homo sapiens (Human)
    ?proteinURI up:organism taxon:9606 .
    # Check if the protein catalyzes a reaction (i.e., is an enzyme)
    # and get the URI of the catalyzed reaction (which is a Rhea reaction URI)
    ?proteinURI up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction .
  }

  # --- Query Rhea endpoint to check if the reaction involves sterol metabolism ---
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Find participants involved in the reaction catalyzed by the human enzyme
    ?reaction rhea:involvedParticipant ?participant .
    # Link the participant to its ChEBI identifier
    ?participant rhea:chebi ?chebiURI .
    # Check if the ChEBI entity is a sterol (CHEBI:15889) or a subclass thereof
    ?chebiURI rdfs:subClassOf* chebi:15889 .
  }
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve drugs that target human enzymes involved in sterol metabolism (federated query with WikiData and Rhea).
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?drug ?drugLabel ?enzyme ?enzymeLabel
WHERE {
  # Step 1: Find human proteins (potential enzymes) and their WikiData links in UniProt
  # We start by filtering for human proteins as the organism constraint is specific to UniProt.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?enzyme a up:Protein ;
            up:organism taxon:9606 ; # Filter for Homo sapiens (taxon ID 9606)
            rdfs:label ?enzymeLabel ; # Get the label for the enzyme
            rdfs:seeAlso ?wikidataItem . # Get the corresponding WikiData item URI for linking
  }

  # Step 2: Find reactions involving sterols and the enzymes catalyzing them in Rhea
  # This step identifies enzymes involved in sterol metabolism.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction rhea:involves chebi:15889 . # Find reactions involving sterol (CHEBI:15889)
    ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?enzyme . # Get the UniProt URI of the enzyme catalyzing the reaction
    # The ?enzyme variable links this reaction to the human protein found in the UniProt service block.
  }

  # Step 3: Find drugs in WikiData that target the enzymes identified
  # This step uses the WikiData link obtained from UniProt to find targeting drugs.
  SERVICE <https://query.wikidata.org/sparql> {

          wdt:P31 wd:Q12140 . # Ensure the item is an instance of 'drug' (Q12140)
    OPTIONAL { ?drug rdfs:label ?drugLabel filter (lang(?drugLabel) = "en") } # Get English label for the drug if available
    # The ?wikidataItem variable links this drug target information back to the UniProt service block.
  }
}

PREFIX taxonomy: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX sl: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>

SELECT DISTINCT ?metabolite
WHERE {
  # Query Rhea for metabolites involved in biochemical reactions known to occur in Homo sapiens
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Find reactions associated with the human taxonomy identifier (Homo sapiens)
    ?reaction rhea:organism taxonomy:9606 ;
              rhea:contains ?participant . # Link the reaction to its participants (substrates/products)
    # Link the participant to the chemical entity involved in the reaction
    # These are typically represented by ChEBI identifiers in Rhea
    ?participant rhea:contains ?metabolite_chebi .
    # Filter to ensure we are getting ChEBI entities, which represent metabolites
    FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?metabolite_chebi), STR(chebi:)))

    BIND(?metabolite_chebi AS ?metabolite)
  }

  # Note: This part lists all lipids in SwissLipids, not strictly filtered by organism,

  SERVICE <https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/> {

    ?lipid_sl a sl:Lipid .

    BIND(?lipid_sl AS ?metabolite)
  }
}

    SERVICE <https://idsm.elixir-czech.cz/sparql/endpoint/chebi> {

].

     ?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rdfs:subClassOf ?chebi .

   # Match the found Rhea reactions with human UniProtKB proteins
   ?protein up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
   ?protein up:organism taxon:9606 .
   # Find only those human entries that have an annotated related disease, and optionaly map these to OMIM
   ?protein up:annotation/up:disease ?disease .

     ?disease rdfs:seeAlso ?omim .
     ?omim up:database <http://purl.uniprot.org/database/MIM>
   }
}

  SERVICE <http://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {

# This query attempts to generate a "draft human metabolome" by listing:

  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {

    ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?uniprotEntry .

  }

    FILTER (STRSTARTS(?japaneseLabel, "Japanese"))

    ?entity skos:altLabel ?englishLabel .

    FILTER (lang(?englishLabel) = "en")
  }
}

PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

  ?ecNumber
  (count(?protein) as ?proteinCount)
  ?reaction
  ?equation
WHERE {
  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:status rh:Approved .
  ?reaction rh:equation ?equation .
  ?reaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
  ?reaction rh:side ?reactionSide .
  ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
  CHEBI:83137 rdfs:subClassOf+ ?chebi.

  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
  ?protein a up:Protein .
  ?protein up:reviewed true .
    {?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:domain/up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:component/up:enzyme ?ecNumber} .
  }
} 
GROUP BY ?chebi ?ecNumber ?reaction ?equation
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql
PREFIX rhea: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX uniprot: <http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> # Common for labels
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> # Common for labels

SELECT DISTINCT ?reaction ?reactionName ?metabolite ?metaboliteRole ?enzyme ?enzymeName
WHERE {
  # Query Rhea for reactions involving the specified metabolite (CHEBI:83137)
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction a rhea:Reaction .
    # Find participants in the reaction
    ?reaction rhea:participant ?participant .
    # Link the participant to the specific metabolite URI
    ?participant rhea:compound chebi:83137 . # CHEBI:83137 corresponds to 'butanoate'
    # Get the role of the metabolite in this reaction (e.g., reactant, product, cofactor)
    ?participant rhea:role ?metaboliteRole .

    # Optional: Get the human-readable name of the reaction
    OPTIONAL { ?reaction rhea:name ?reactionName . }

    # Find the enzyme that catalyzes this reaction
    ?reaction rhea:catalyzedBy ?enzyme .
  }

  # Bind the metabolite URI for the result set
  BIND(chebi:83137 AS ?metabolite)

  # Query UniProt to get details about the catalyzing enzyme
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    # Ensure the found entity is a protein in UniProt
    ?enzyme a up:Protein .
    # Get the recommended full name of the protein
    OPTIONAL { ?enzyme up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?enzymeNameRec . }
    # If recommended name is not available, get the protein name
    OPTIONAL { ?enzyme up:proteinName ?enzymeNameProtein . }
    # Use COALESCE to prefer the recommended name
    BIND(COALESCE(?enzymeNameRec, ?enzymeNameProtein) AS ?enzymeName)
  }
}

  }

  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:status rh:Approved .
  ?reaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
